The infra folder has two JSON files simply because they represent two different dashboards:

    - home.json – a very simple “Infra Home” dashboard you can set as default home (via default_home_dashboard_path). This is the landing page for infra users.

    - k8s-overview.json – a separate “Kubernetes Overview” dashboard focusing on cluster health (nodes, pods, API server, etc.), which you may link from the home dashboard or bookmark separately.

You could think of infra as the “infrastructure team’s space” in Grafana:

    - One dashboard is a general entry point (home).

    - The other is a more detailed view for a specific concern (Kubernetes).

There is nothing special about having exactly two; it just mirrors a common pattern:

    - One high‑level summary dashboard.

    - One or more focus dashboards (Kubernetes, nodes, networking, etc.)
